doublethink (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release: M1 secure pub/sub broker.
  * Private channels with Ed25519 challenge/response authentication and
    per-channel authorisation (knowing a channel name grants no access).
  * Broker-blind end-to-end encryption of private-channel payloads
    (X25519 ECDH, per-direction NaCl secretbox); the broker never sees plaintext.
  * MITM-resistant pairing: single-use, short-TTL invite codes plus an
    out-of-band short authentication string (SAS) confirmed before a peer's key
    is admitted.
  * Opt-in plaintext public topics, ntfy-style (HTTP POST publish, SSE subscribe).
  * Bidirectional, asynchronous, streaming delivery; barge-in control is not
    blocked behind a peer's stream.

